result.name: BigFish Seafood & Grill

reviews.text: Good place for seafood or overall grill fare. Food is rather high quality fusion, and while not cheap the prices aren't exorbitant either. The outdoor seating is nice, as is the decor indoors. Service is nice and friendly as well. One thing to keep in mind is that the portions are rather small. When we visited, or group has already had snacks before but found no challenge finishing a starter, three oysters and two mains each.
The food is great but I would recommend to eat the fish meals, they're the best

Disastrous meal!
The creme brulee has a bit of plastic taste and doesn’t have the crust on top! I cannot have the 2nd bite... 
The beef in the ragu was overcooked and extremely dry. 
The fish in the seafood pasta was really really bad. Had a taste of after freeze.

Plenty of seating outdoors and indoors, large and varied menu and great staff.

We had the chicken tikka salad, a seafood pizza and soup of the day (broccoli). All tasted good and we especially liked the salad. 

Price was a reasonable HK$304.

This is my favourite place for oysters and bubbles. The seafood is very fresh and lots of choices. Best of all is the service. Nothing is a problem for the staff. Highly recommended a visit if you are in Sai Kung and ready for a feast.
